tindivanam flyover is asia's second railways flyover. it has roundana and four lanes. the flyover is located in heart of the tindivanam, between nh 66 (bangalore - pondicherry) and nh 45 (chennai - dindukkal). this flyover was inaugurated by tamil nadu chief minister mr. m. karunanithi in the 2000. this flyover was constructed at a cost of rs.22 crores.